'''Cadmium''' was a type of [[Metal/Legends|metal]].<ref name="DES">''[[Dark Empire Sourcebook]]''</ref> At some point between [[0 ABY/Legends|0 ABY]] and [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]],<ref name="Dates">''[[Dark Empire Sourcebook]]'' dates [[Umak Leth]]'s presentation of the [[molecular furnace]] design concept to between the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]] and the [[Battle of Endor/Legends|Battle of Endor]], which corresponds to between [[0 ABY/Legends|0 ABY]] and [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]] per ''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''.</ref> [[Umak Leth]], [[Chief engineer/Legends|Chief Engineer]] to [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]] of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]], perfected a design concept of a [[molecular furnace]]. The design incorporated [[intrinsic force negator]]s that would separate matter into its constituent elements, after which those materials would be stored in [[force bubble]]s of metals such as cadmium. Palpatine was pleased with the presentation of the concept and ordered Leth to begin work on a [[Weapon/Legends|weapons]] platform to be built around the molecular furnace&mdash;a project that would ultimately evolve into the [[World Devastator]] [[Superweapon/Legends|superweapons]].<ref name="DES" />

==Behind the scenes==
Cadmium was mentioned in the ''[[Dark Empire Sourcebook]]'', [[Michael Allen Horne]]'s [[1993]] sourcebook published by [[West End Games]] for use with ''[[Star Wars: The Roleplaying Game]]''.<ref name="DES" /> In the real world, [[Wikipedia:Cadmium|cadmium]] is a soft [[Wikipedia:Metal|metal]] and [[Wikipedia:Chemical element|chemical element]] with a [[Wikipedia:Melting point|melting point]] of 321 [[Wikipedia:Celsius|degrees Celsius]].<ref name="CadmiumBritannica">{{WebCite|url=https://www.britannica.com/science/cadmium|text=Cadmium &#124; Uses, Properties, & Facts|author=The Editors of Encyclopædia Britannica|date=2024-11-29|work=[[Wikipedia:Encyclopædia Britannica|''Encyclopædia Britannica'']]|archivedate=20241115081435}}</ref>

